WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.400
This is part two of using Kordo for presenting your analytics work. Kordo helps you publish

00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:09.920
your technical work beautifully anywhere, including helping you build beautiful slides.

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:13.360
Now, there's nice support for PowerPoint and Beamer LaTeX slides, but let me quickly run

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:17.840
through a few slide options with Reveal.js. With just a bit of markup in your Jupyter

00:00:17.840 --> 00:00:23.600
Notebook, CodeScript, or RMacadoc, you can make incremental lists, pretty code chunks,

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:28.639
including line highlighting, animate your presentations with code animations and animation

00:00:28.639 --> 00:00:33.759
fragments, and add smooth slide transitions. And of course, you can execute your code and

00:00:33.759 --> 00:00:38.000
show that output, whether that output is a static plot or something more interactive,

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:42.560
maybe even a map or some other widget. Kordo makes it easy to show LaTeX equations,

00:00:42.560 --> 00:00:48.400
have custom layouts, image layout options, slide backgrounds. There's auto-animation options,

00:00:48.400 --> 00:00:52.799
interactive tab sets inside your slides. You have many theme and customization options to

00:00:52.799 --> 00:00:58.480
style your slides. There are admin navigation options, interactive chalkboard. There's a nice

00:00:58.480 --> 00:01:00.160
speaker view and, of course, speaker.

